        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 3:39PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 338 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Stonington, or 16 miles southwest of The Saunders Elevator, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stonington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
